WEBVTT

00:04.265 --> 00:04.482
.

00:04.526 --> 00:06.484
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:06.528 --> 00:07.790
sexually based offenses

00:07.833 --> 00:09.487
are considered
especially heinous.

00:09.531 --> 00:11.707
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:11.750 --> 00:13.578
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:13.622 --> 00:15.145
are members of an elite squad

00:15.189 --> 00:17.060
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:17.104 --> 00:18.888
These are their stories.

00:20.063 --> 00:22.500
- The defendant has means
and reason to flee, Your Honor.

00:22.544 --> 00:24.372
He's facing 25 years
on Rape One.

00:24.415 --> 00:27.592
- My client is eager to go
to trial and clear his name.

00:27.636 --> 00:30.682
- This is ridiculous.
It was consensual.

00:30.726 --> 00:32.032
She never said "No."

00:32.075 --> 00:34.643
- The victim's blood alcohol
was 0.23.

00:34.686 --> 00:36.079
- We were both drunk.

00:36.123 --> 00:37.167
- That's it, Mr. Madden.

00:37.211 --> 00:38.386
Mr. Stone, I'm granting

00:38.429 --> 00:39.735
your request for a remand.

00:42.259 --> 00:44.348
- You're going to jail, sir.

00:51.225 --> 00:53.357
You believe me?

00:53.401 --> 00:55.490
I never wanted that,
not with him.

00:55.533 --> 00:56.882
- I do.

00:56.926 --> 00:59.711
- We'll be in touch
about your testimony, okay?

01:01.757 --> 01:04.107
- Well done.

01:04.151 --> 01:05.761
- She was afraid
he was gonna get out on bail.

01:05.804 --> 01:08.111
Amazing, get a remand
on the he-said, she-said.

01:08.155 --> 01:09.852
- Yeah. Moral,
don't piss off the judge.

01:11.158 --> 01:12.115
I can download you
on where we are

01:12.159 --> 01:13.464
on the investigation.

01:13.508 --> 01:15.205
- Yeah, I do, but I'm trying
to slow it down.

01:15.249 --> 01:16.554
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Have a good night, okay?

01:16.598 --> 01:18.730
- All right.

01:19.949 --> 01:21.864
Tad.

01:21.907 --> 01:23.909
Hey. The works.

01:23.953 --> 01:25.868
- Oh, my God.

01:25.911 --> 01:27.043
It is you.

01:27.087 --> 01:28.218
Peter Stone.

01:29.872 --> 01:30.829
- You pitched for the Cubs.

01:30.873 --> 01:31.830
- I did.

01:31.874 --> 01:32.875
- Grew up in Chicago.

01:32.918 --> 01:35.007
My dad took me to every game.

01:35.051 --> 01:36.661
- That's a lot
of baseball games.

01:36.705 --> 01:37.662
Thank you.

01:37.706 --> 01:38.663
- I can't believe it.

01:38.707 --> 01:40.317
I have to call my dad.

01:41.623 --> 01:45.061
Any chance I could
buy you a drink?

01:45.105 --> 01:47.019
- Yeah. Yeah.

01:47.063 --> 01:48.020
Here you go, Tad.

01:48.064 --> 01:49.021
Thanks.

01:49.065 --> 01:50.022
I happen to know a place

01:50.066 --> 01:52.373
right around the corner.

01:52.416 --> 01:54.810
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

01:54.853 --> 01:56.420
- It's delicious.

01:56.464 --> 01:59.771
Now I know what all
the truffle fuss is about.

01:59.815 --> 02:01.599
- Italian white truffles
in November.

02:01.643 --> 02:03.514
If you say so.

02:03.558 --> 02:05.995
We weren't big on
truffle risotto in Georgia.

02:06.038 --> 02:07.257
- Yeah, more like
shrimp and grits.

02:07.301 --> 02:09.955
- Yeah. Oh, you've been
listening.

02:09.999 --> 02:12.262
- So what looks good
for dessert?

02:12.306 --> 02:14.438
- Oh...

02:14.482 --> 02:17.006
